text: Marshall County is a county in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2020 census, 33,752 people lived there. Its county seat is Holly Springs. The county is named for Chief Justice of the United States John Marshall. == References == == Other websites == * Official website of Marshall County *McAlexander/Marshall County Collection (MUM00287) owned by the University of Mississippi, Archives and Special Collections.
